.TH "usb_disable_device" 9 "usb_disable_device" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
usb_disable_device \- Disable all the endpoints for a USB device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" usb_disable_device
.BI "(struct usb_device *dev "  ","
.BI "int skip_ep0 "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
the device whose endpoints are being disabled
.IP "skip_ep0" 12
0 to disable endpoint 0, 1 to skip it.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Disables all the device's endpoints, potentially including endpoint 0.
Deallocates hcd/hardware state for the endpoints (nuking all or most
pending urbs) and usbcore state for the interfaces, so that usbcore
must \fBusb_set_configuration\fP before any interfaces could be used.
